# Overview

Cybersecurity offers many career paths. Each role focuses on protecting systems, networks, applications, or data from cyber threats. Choosing a career depends on your interests, technical skills, and long-term goals.

---

# Why Cyber Security?

- High demand for skilled professionals
- Opportunities in different industries
- Continuous learning and problem-solving
- Competitive salaries
- Ability to help organizations defend against cyber attacks

---

# Common Career Paths

## 1. Security Analyst (SOC Analyst)

### Responsibilities

- Monitor security alerts
- Analyze suspicious activities
- Investigate incidents
- Respond to security events
- Report vulnerabilities

### Skills

- Networking
- Windows & Linux
- SIEM tools
- Log Analysis
- Incident Response

---

## 2. Security Engineer

### Responsibilities

- Design secure systems
- Configure firewalls
- Implement security controls
- Improve infrastructure security

### Skills

- Networking
- Firewalls
- IDS/IPS
- Cloud Security
- System Administration

---

## 3. Penetration Tester (Ethical Hacker)

### Responsibilities

- Perform authorized security testing
- Identify vulnerabilities
- Simulate cyber attacks
- Write security assessment reports

### Skills

- Linux
- Networking
- Web Security
- Python
- Burp Suite
- Nmap
- Metasploit

---

## 4. Incident Responder

### Responsibilities

- Investigate cyber attacks
- Contain security incidents
- Recover affected systems
- Document findings

### Skills

- Digital Forensics
- Log Analysis
- Malware Investigation
- Communication

---

## 5. Digital Forensics Analyst

### Responsibilities

- Collect digital evidence
- Analyze compromised devices
- Recover deleted data
- Support investigations

### Skills

- File Systems
- Operating Systems
- Evidence Handling
- Forensic Tools

---

## 6. Malware Analyst

### Responsibilities

- Analyze malicious software
- Understand malware behavior
- Detect threats
- Develop detection methods

### Skills

- Reverse Engineering
- Assembly Language
- Windows Internals
- Programming

---

## 7. Security Consultant

### Responsibilities

- Assess organizational security
- Recommend improvements
- Conduct risk assessments
- Develop security policies

### Skills

- Risk Management
- Communication
- Security Frameworks
- Compliance

---

## 8. Red Team

### Responsibilities

- Simulate real-world attacks
- Test organizational defenses
- Identify security weaknesses

### Skills

- Penetration Testing
- Social Engineering
- Active Directory
- Exploitation

---

## 9. Blue Team

### Responsibilities

- Monitor security systems
- Detect attacks
- Respond to incidents
- Strengthen defenses

### Skills

- SIEM
- Threat Hunting
- Incident Response
- Network Monitoring

---

# Offensive vs Defensive Security

| Offensive Security        | Defensive Security            |
|---------------------------|-------------------------------|
| Attacks systems ethically | Protects systems from attacks |
| Finds vulnerabilities     | Detects and blocks threatsmmm |
| Penetration Testing       | Security Monitoring           |
| Red Team                  | Blue Team                     |

